input:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Fiona : obj
constant Harry : obj

constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Blue Anne
axiom T2 : Kind Anne
axiom T3 : Nice Anne
axiom T4 : Quiet Anne
axiom T5 : Rough Anne
axiom T6 : Young Anne
axiom T7 : Red Erin
axiom T8 : Kind Fiona
axiom T9 : Rough Fiona
axiom T10 : Kind Harry
axiom T11 : Red Harry
axiom T12 : Young Harry

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Red x → Nice x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Blue x → Young x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Kind x
axiom R4 : Nice Erin ∧ Quiet Erin → Rough Erin
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ Quiet x → Blue x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Quiet x

theorem erin_is_not_kind : ¬ Kind Erin :=
begin
  sorry,
end
output:
theorem erin_is_not_kind : ¬ Kind Erin :=
begin
  intro H,
  have H1 : Quiet Erin := R6 Erin T7,
  have H2 : Nice Erin := R1 Erin (and.intro H1 T7),
  have H3 : Rough Erin := R4 (and.intro H2 H1),
  have H4 : ¬ Rough Erin := λ _, H,
  exact H4 H3,
end

-- The answer is True
